{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "SATP - Asset Schema Architecture for Asset Exchanges",
    "version": "0.0.1",
    "description": "SATP is a protocol operating between two gateways that conducts the transfer of a digital asset from one gateway to another. The protocol establishes a secure channel between the endpoints and implements a 2-phase commit to ensure the properties of transfer atomicity, consistency, isolation and durability.\nThe Asset Schema Architecture for Asset Exchanges defines the data structures and schemas used in the SATP protocol. It provides a standardized way to represent assets, their properties, and the transactions that involve them. It is designed to be flexible and extensible, allowing for the representation of a wide variety of asset types and their associated metadata.\n\nThis API defines the registry, asset schema authority and asset provider facing APIs.\n\n**Additional Resources**:\n- [Asset Schema Architecture for Asset Exchange](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-avrilionis-satp-asset-schema-architecture-06)\n- [Asset Profiles for Asset Exchange draft](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-avrilionis-satp-asset-profiles/)",
    "contact": {
      "name": "Hyperledger Cacti"
    },
    "x-logo": {
      "altText": "Cacti logo",
      "backgroundColor": "#fafafa",
      "url": "https://github.com/hyperledger/cacti/blob/main/images/HL_Cacti_Logo_Color.png"
    }
  },
  "externalDocs": {
    "description": "For more information about the SATP Gateway Client, refer to the official documentation.",
    "url": "https://github.com/hyperledger/cacti/tree/main/packages/cactus-plugin-satp-hermes/README.md"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "http://{host}:{port}/api/@hyperledger/cacti-asset-schema-architecture/registry",
      "description": "Registry server",
      "variables": {
